FBIS4-48524 "drafr098_c_94018" FBIS-AFR-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Police Officers Commit To Upholding Constitution Police Officers Commit To Upholding Constitution MB1905181694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 19 May 94 MB1905181694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] Senior police officers have committed themselves to upholding the constitution and fighting against crime and violence. The commitments were made this morning during discussions between the minister of safety and security, Mr. Sydney Mufamadi, and his deputy, Mr. Joe Matthews. The police said in a statement that members would work together in a professional, unbiased, and apolitical way in the service of the community. The senior officers assured all policemen that they would be handled in a reasonable and fair way at all times.
